✅ Major Issues Cloud Support Engineers Face (Day-to-Day)
1. Networking & Connectivity Issues

Problem: Customer’s EC2 instance (AWS) or VM (Azure) cannot connect to the internet or other services.
Root Causes:

Misconfigured security groups/firewall rules.
Wrong routing tables or NAT gateway setup.
DNS resolution failures.


Resolution: Check VPC settings, security groups, route tables, DNS configs.


2. Storage & Disk Issues

Problem: Application crashes due to full disk or incorrect mount points.
Root Causes:

EBS volume not attached or mounted properly.
Incorrect permissions on storage buckets (S3, Blob).


Resolution: Resize volumes, remount disks, fix IAM policies.


3. IAM & Permission Errors

Problem: Customer cannot access resources or API calls fail.
Root Causes:

Misconfigured IAM roles/policies.
Missing permissions for service accounts.


Resolution: Review IAM policies, grant least privilege access.


4. Service Outages or Latency

Problem: Application is slow or unavailable.
Root Causes:

Regional service outage.
Overloaded resources (CPU, memory).


Resolution: Scale resources, check health dashboards, suggest failover strategies.


5. Billing & Cost Optimization

Problem: Customer complains about unexpected high bills.
Root Causes:

Unused resources running (EC2, RDS).
Misconfigured autoscaling.


Resolution: Analyze cost reports, recommend reserved instances or autoscaling policies.


6. Deployment & CI/CD Issues

Problem: Application deployment fails in cloud pipeline.
Root Causes:

Incorrect container image tags.
Misconfigured Kubernetes networking.


Resolution: Debug pipeline logs, fix YAML configs, check container registry.


7. Backup & Disaster Recovery

Problem: Data loss or backup failure.
Root Causes:

Snapshot not scheduled.
Incorrect replication settings.


Resolution: Configure automated backups, enable cross-region replication.


8. SSL/TLS Certificate Issues

Problem: Website shows “Not Secure” or HTTPS fails.
Root Causes:

Expired SSL certificate.
Misconfigured load balancer.


Resolution: Renew certificates, update LB settings.


9. API Rate Limits & Throttling

Problem: Customer’s API calls fail intermittently.
Root Causes:

Exceeded API rate limits.


Resolution: Suggest exponential backoff, request quota increase.


10. Monitoring & Alerts

Problem: Customer receives too many alerts or none at all.
Root Causes:

Misconfigured CloudWatch/Log Analytics.


Resolution: Tune alert thresholds, set up dashboards.
